{"key":"processedPost-6995376","value":{"id":6995376,"first":6995267,"last":6995376,"when":1180721612,"utime":"06/01/07 09:13 PM","content":"And. . .If you do the 24 to 36 hour soak, you'll rarely get burst kernels, even if you boil rapidly, because the kernels are already fully hydrated as agar said.<br /><br />I use rye, and after the soak, bring it to a boil for the reasons agar said, so the kernels will dry off after they are dumped into the collander. The other reason for boiling is so you don't pour the stinky bacterial water down your sink drain, making the p-trap stink like fermented grain.  Boiling kills off the live bacteria, giving a mini pre-sterilization.<br />RR","title":"Re: WBS simmered too long...many kernels cracked","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}